<table width="1160" border="0"><tr><td width="302"><img src="../Pictures/lion.png" width="300" height="384" alt="Lion Photo"></td><td width="848"><p id ="main_contents">Lions have strong, compact bodies and powerful forelegs, teeth, and jaws for pulling down<br><br><br>and killing prey. Their fur is yellowish gold and the male lions manes are shappy and have<br><br><br>different colors anywhere from  blond to brown to black. Their manes are determined by color<br><br><br>depending on their age, genetics and hormones. Young lions are spotted and this will<br><br><br>disappear as they get older.<br><br><br><br><strong>Size:</strong> Male lions are much larger in size which is about 20 feet in length. Female lions are<br><br><br>only 9 feet in length.<br><br><br><strong>National Zoo Diet:</strong> Keepers feed the Zoo's lions beef and during their stay at the zoo they<br><br><br>are given bones twice a week.</p></td></tr></table></div></div><br>
	
